Basic Discription of java:-
      Java is a high-level, object-oriented programming language used to develop software applications such as web applications, mobile apps, desktop programs, and enterprise systems.

JDB (Java Development Kit):-
  JDB (Java Debugger) is a command-line debugging tool used to find and fix errors (bugs) in Java programs. 🐞
  It is part of the JDK (Java Development Kit).

  1️⃣ Purpose of JDB
        JDB helps programmers to:
        Detect errors in a program
        Stop the program at a specific line
        Check variable values
        Execute code step by step
        This process is called debugging.
          
JRE (Java Runtime Environment):-
    JRE is the environment required to run Java programs.
    It provides the libraries and components needed to execute Java applications. ☕

    1️⃣ Components of JRE
        JRE mainly contains:
        1. JVM (Java Virtual Machine)
          Executes the Java bytecode.
        
        2. Core Class Libraries
          Provides predefined classes used in Java programs.
        
        3. Supporting Files
          Required to run Java applications.

JVM(Java Virtual Machine):-
    JVM is a virtual machine that runs Java programs.
    It converts Java bytecode into machine code so the computer can execute it. ☕
    
